The paper discusses the challenge of understanding the content of an RDF graph, which is a common problem in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents eLinda, which is an explorer for Linked Data, and this tool involves working with databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the visualization of data, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and information systems (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the integration of applications with RDF graphs, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
